ManipulAR - Notices and acknowledgements

ManipulAR is a CW trainer and electronic keyer project for Arduino.

This project is inspired by:

- cw-trainer by Mike Hughes, KC1DMR
  https://github.com/mfhughes128/cw-trainer

- Arduino CW Trainer by Tom Lewis, N4TL
  Published in QST magazine, September 2016

ManipulAR includes a local modified copy of:

- MorseEnDecoder by raron
  Original copyright notice and GNU GPLv3 license header are preserved
  in MorseEnDecoder.cpp and MorseEnDecoder.h.

The local changes to MorseEnDecoder are intended to allow runtime tone
frequency adjustment from the ManipulAR preferences menu.

ManipulAR should be distributed with its source code and with the GNU GPLv3
license text included in this repository.
